Social Development Minister Bathabile Dlamini has sent a very strong message, saying that if nothing is done about women abuse there will be more cases like that of Karabo Mokoena.The 22-year-old&#8217;s burnt body was discovered in Lyndhurst last month her boyfriend Sandile Mantsoe has been arrested for her murder. Dlamini is among the dignitaries at Mokoena&#8217;s funeral service underway in Diepkloof Soweto on Friday.She says there s a genocide against women in this country.The minister says if nothing is done soon to address women abuse, women will continue to raped, murdered and victimised. Dlamini says she doesn&#8217;t necessarily agree with the social media hashtag #menaretrash. I m totally against the hashtag men are trash. Minister for Women in the Presidency Susan Shabangu is also in attendance here. The 22-year-old will be laid to rest at the Westpark Cemetery later today.